%N A396779 Distinct x*y, where no pair (x,y) exists such that x + y or |x - y| are squares.
%C A396779 All prime terms are in A070303.
%e A396779 33 is a term since 33+1, 33-1, 11+3 and 11-3 are not squares.
%p A396779 filter:= proc(x)
%p A396779   andmap(t -> t^2 > x or ( not issqr(t + x/t) and not issqr(x/t - t)), NumberTheory:-Divisors(x))
%p A396779 end proc:
%p A396779 select(filter, [$1..200]); # _Robert Israel_, Jul 13 2026
%o A396779 (PARI) isok(k) = fordiv(k, d, if (issquare(d+k/d) || issquare(abs(d-k/d)), return(0))); 1; \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jul 12 2026
